rComments: As a statistics major student, I would like to suggest everyone to think twice before choosing his course. How do I say, this guy's notes is significantly incomprehensible, not to mention that he refuses to answer student questions with harsh attitude. His negative attitude towards teaching just surprised me. He does not deserve that high title.

Record his lectures and ask him a lot of questions. He is a  fair prof and his teaching is better than most stats profs at UofT. I learned a lot from you. He keeps the average down in quizzes and midterms so that he can keep the final easy. Having an easy final is a lot better than hard final.
Difficult to understand, does not post full solutions to practice questions so it's very hard to study. Textbook sucks.

He complains about how tired he is all the time, and therefore does not want us to ask questions during breaks. A lot of my other profs have 3-hour lectures and they don't complain to the students. His tests and quizzes are super hard, and he changes his mind about "bell-curve" 10 times a day. Worst prof I've had in 3 years.
